# Nexus Digital Agents - Orchestration Rules

## Overview

This directory contains the specifications for the Nexus Digital Agents system. These agents work collaboratively to develop, maintain, and improve your project.

## Agent Specifications Location

All agent specifications are located in the `nexus-agents/agents/` directory:

### Core Technical Team
- **Architect** (Principal Engineer) - System design, architecture decisions, technology selection
- **Atlas** (DevOps Engineer) - CI/CD, infrastructure, deployment, monitoring
- **Forge** (Backend Engineer) - API integration, data services, backend logic
- **Guardian** (Security Analyst) - Security reviews, vulnerability assessment, compliance
- **Prism** (Frontend Engineer) - UI components, React development, accessibility, performance
- **Sentinel** (QA Engineer) - Testing strategy, test implementation, quality assurance

### Product & Design Team (MVP - Immediate)
- **Catalyst** (Product Owner) - Product vision, user research, feature prioritization
- **Aura** (UX/UI Designer) - User experience design, visual design, usability testing

### Analytics & Compliance (Production-Ready - Short-term)
- **Insight** (Data Analyst) - User behavior analysis, metrics, A/B testing
- **Beacon** (Accessibility Specialist) - WCAG compliance, assistive technology expertise

### Documentation & Strategy (Enterprise - Long-term)
- **Scribe** (Technical Writer) - Documentation, user guides, developer materials
- **Strategist** (Business Analyst) - Market research, business strategy, competitive analysis

